===2000 census===
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2" /> of 2000, and there were 5,013 people, 1,455 households, and 1,223 families residing in the CDP. The population density was {{convert|3,704.7|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 1,494 housing units at an average density of {{convert|1,104.1|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the CDP was 40.00% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 48.41% [[African American (U.S. Census)|Black or African American]], 0.30% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 3.41% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 4.15% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 3.73% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 11.67% of the population.

There were 1,455 households, out of which 43.6% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 62.2% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 17.0% had a female householder with no husband present, and 15.9% were non-families. 13.0% of all households were made up of individuals, and 5.2% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 3.42 and the average family size was 3.67.

In the CDP, the population was spread out, with 30.3% under the age of 18, 8.1% from 18 to 24, 29.9% from 25 to 44, 23.8% from 45 to 64, and 7.9% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 35 years. For every 100 females, there were 95.1 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 89.3 males.

The median income for a household in the CDP was $99,583. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $30,726. About 3.4% of families and 4.8% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 7.6% of those under age 18 and 8.3% of those age 65 or over.

